===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|uncountable}} an attitude of consideration or high [[regard#Noun|regard]]
#: ''He is an intellectual giant, and I have great '''respect''' for him.''
#: ''we do respect people for their dignity and worth.''
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} good opinion, honor, or admiration
# {{lb|en|uncountable|always plural}} Polite [[greetings]], often offered as [[condolences]] after a death.
#: ''The mourners paid their last '''respects''' to the deceased poet.''
# {{lb|en|countable}} a particular [[aspect]] of something
#: ''This year's model is superior to last year's in several '''respects'''.''

